{[%evp 0,26,28,28,69,-21,-21,-29,0,-32,6,-24,-18,-27,31,39,50,22,25,25,25,25,25,25,108,61,61,69,69] Black to move} 5... d5 $1 {Of course.} 6. fxe4 {Now giving up the bishop pair with 6. Bxf6 would be even worse considering how open is the position now.} Nxe4 $1 {[%cal Yg7d4,Yf8f1,Gb8c6,Gf8g7] Taking with the pawn might mean suffering after Qd2-0-0-0 and a long game ahead. We want to create some fast pressure on d4 and also use the f file in our benefit.} 7. Nxe4 dxe4 8. Bc4 Nc6 $15 {[%cal Gc6a5] It's very important to have the Nc6-Na5 idea in mind, as sometimes we would require it to castle. Black is completely fine and White doesn't is too slow to finish development.} *

