{[%evp 0,29,27,27,70,72,59,61,78,65,115,50,71,63,64,43,33,-2,50,27,19,48,29,27,29,35,29,-1,12,35,28,44] [#]} {Black to move} 5... Nc6 $1 {[%cal Gd8e7,Gc8d7] I give this new move. We want to switch the plan playing Bd7-Qe7-0-0-0. This way g2-g4 is far less effective.} 6. g4 Qe7 {[%cal Ge6e5]} 7. gxf5 (7. Qf3 {This is an example if White wants to be ambitious.} e5 8. Bg5 fxg4 9. hxg4 Bxg4 $1 10. Qg2 exd4 11. Nd5 Qf7 $132) (7. Bg2 g6 $5 {[%cal Gc8d7,Gf8g7,Gc6d8,Gd8f7,Gg6f5] We have a very nice maneouvring position.}) 7... e5 $1 {And black is already better.} *

