{[%evp 0,30,28,24,69,49,49,49,50,48,63,63,64,78,66,71,66,38,41,36,35,29,51,40,40,40,47,41,52,60,51,54,59] [#]} {Black to move} 10... Nxe5 11. Bxe5 Nd6 $1 {[%cal Gd6c4] A theme usually seen in the Catalan with Bb4+, Be7 and eventually Ne4. We force the pawn exchange or taking a pawn. It has excellent results recently.} 12. b3 Nf7 $146 {[%cal Gf7e5,Gb7b6] This move is excellent and black equalizes comfortably. White exchanged his best knight and did not advance at all on the queenside.} 13. Bf4 b6 {[%cal Gc8a6,Ge7f6] Followed by Ba6 and then even g5 or Bf6. White has a silly knight on c3 and I don't see a way to make any progress.} *

